description:
&lt;p&gt;The Practice Development Team is looking to appoint a dynamic and innovative full time Clinical Education Facilitator with a passion for education, training and developing learners in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have recent critical care experience and skills, to work alongside all staff members to facilitate the development and maintenance of a positive practice environment.The candidate should have high level self-management skills, including time management, prioritisation and organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills are essential to build on the networks required for the role. You will be expected to work in collaboration with speciality nursing teams and Higher Education Institute to ensure good working partnerships. This will be an opportunity for self –development in leading change and team management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a passion for supporting both clinical and professional development and improving patient care we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLauren StringerJob titleProfessional Development senior sisterEmail addresslauen.stringer@nhs.netTelephone number01902698505Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Sara Lawley, Operational Manager on 01902 307999 extension 6603&lt;/p&gt;
